## Early game

**Akkad** on Eris (Dark Sector Defense, Infested Ship tileset) is a classic
low-level Nano Spore farm: its dense Infested waves drop Nano Spores as enemy
loot, and the Dark Sector's resource-chance bonus stacks on top. Because it's
an enemy drop, a Resource Drop Booster and a Nekros or Khora in the squad
(re-rolling extra drops with Desecrate/Pilfer) meaningfully raise the haul —
a few rounds already yield thousands.

## Mid & late game

**Piscinas** on Saturn (Dark Sector Survival, Grineer Asteroid tileset, levels
26-36) is the best per-hour spot once a squad can run Steel Path: the Dark
Sector's resource-chance bonus plus Steel Path Infested density means a Nekros
or Khora meaningfully boosts the haul by re-rolling the enemy drops. Long
Survival rotations outperform resetting the mission, since Nano Spores
accumulate quickly the longer you stay — and boosters, the Steel Path passive
and the loot frame all stack because these are enemy drops.

